<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Locality of sampling sites for Eosamon daiae sp. nov. and Indochinamon malipoense sp. nov. in southwestern and southeastern Yunnan Province, China." , "Figure 6. Habitat of Eosamon daiae sp. nov., the moist mud burrows at the type locality, Tianbao Town, Yunnan Province, China." , "Figure 5. The ventral view of left G 1 A Eosamon daiae sp. nov. holotype, male, 26.6 x 22.2 mm, NNU 190503 B Eosamon tumidum, male, 23.2 x 18.7 mm, IZCAS CB 11382 C Eosamon lushuiense, male, 23.7 x 19.9 mm, NNU 162821 D Eosamon tengchongense, male, 37.9 x 30.1 mm, NNU 193261. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." , "Figure 2. Eosamon daiae sp. nov. holotype, male, 26.6 x 22.2 mm, NNU 190503 A dorsal view B frontal view of cephalothorax C ventral view showing anterior thoracic sternum and pleon. Scale bars: 1.0 cm." , "Figure 4. Eosamon daiae sp. nov. paratype, female, 20.1 x 16.5 mm, NNU 190505 A abdomen B vulvae. Scale bars: 1.0 cm (A); 1.0 mm (B)." , "Figure 3. Eosamon daiae sp. nov. holotype, male, 26.6 x 22.2 mm, NNU 190503 A left third maxilliped B left G 1 (ventral view) C left G 1 (dorsal view) D left G 2 E sterno-abdominal cavity with G 1 in situ F G 1 terminal segment (ventral view). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467893" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467890" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467894" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467891" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467892" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467895" .

